-- ABU DHABI XL
UPDATE tours SET description = 'Our tour begins with a scenic walk along Abu Dhabi''s waterfront, known as the Corniche, which will give you an extraordinary view of the city skyline. Here we will make a brief stop to capture some photographs, before continuing to the Heritage Village. This place is a fascinating reconstruction of a village that offers an immersion into the past, allowing us to relive the country''s lifestyle before the discovery of oil. 

Next we will stop for another photo session at the Emirates Palace, a sumptuous 5-star hotel originally conceived as a royal residence. After that we will stop at the Etihad Towers, five imposing towers that represent an icon of Abu Dhabi city.

Our next destination will be the majestic Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque, also known as the White Mosque. This authentic architectural masterpiece is considered one of the most beautiful mosques in the world and can accommodate up to 40,000 worshippers. Please note that access is only allowed with appropriate clothing.

We continue the tour to Yas Island, which is home to the Formula 1 Circuit and Ferrari World, where we will make a photo stop and visit the Ferrari gadget shop. The last stop of our tour will be a photo-stop at the Louvre Museum, an architectural masterpiece by Archi-Star Jean Nouvel.

Tour highlights: The Corniche, Heritage Village, Emirates Palace, Etihad Towers, Sheikh Zayed Grand Mosque, Ferrari World, Louvre Museum.

Note: For mosque entry, women must wear long sleeves and long pants with a headscarf, while men must wear long pants. The itinerary may vary based on traffic conditions.' 
WHERE name = 'ABU DHABI XL';

-- DUBAI XL  
UPDATE tours SET description = 'Venture to discover Dubai with a complete tour that will take you from its glittering skyscrapers to the historic streets of the souqs, for an authentic and evocative experience. We start the journey at Dubai Marina, where you can admire the imposing skyscrapers that symbolize the modernity and luxury of the city.

We will continue towards Palm Jumeirah, the palm-shaped artificial island, where VIP and celebrity residences are located. Here we will make a photo stop at Atlantis The Palm, one of the most iconic hotels in the world. The tour continues with an external visit to the legendary Burj Al Arab, the famous "Sail", followed by a walk in the suggestive Souq Madinat Jumeirah, a place that recreates the atmosphere of traditional markets with boutiques and shops overlooking water channels.

Traveling along Sheikh Zayed Road, the beating heart of the city, we will stop for a photo stop at the Museum of the Future and the majestic Dubai Frame, the world''s largest golden frame, perfect for a memorable shot. We then enter the historic heart of Dubai with a visit to the Bastakia district, where you can explore the ancient Emirati houses and immerse yourself in the city''s history.

We will cross the Creek aboard an Abra, the traditional wooden boat, to reach the city''s historic souqs. You will walk among the Gold Souq, where you can admire the world''s largest gold ring, the Spice Souq, with its exotic aromas and the Textile Souq, among precious and colorful fabrics.

The tour concludes in the vibrant Dubai Mall with a photo stop in front of the Burj Khalifa, the world''s tallest skyscraper. You will have time to visit the giant aquarium and watch the dancing fountains show, a magical combination of water, music and lights.

Tour highlights: Dubai Marina, The Point Atlantis, Palm Jumeirah, Souq Madinat Jumeirah & Burj Al Arab, Al Bastakiya Historic Quarter & Al Fahidi, Abra ride on Dubai Creek, Gold & Spice Souqs, Sheikh Zayed Road, Museum of the Future, Dubai Frame, Dubai Mall, Burj Khalifa photo stop, Dancing Fountains.' 
WHERE name = 'DUBAI XL';

