-- MANAMA CITY
UPDATE tours SET description = 'Our tour begins with a visit to the Bahrain National Museum, inaugurated in 1988 and considered one of the most important in the Gulf region. Here you can explore dynamic exhibitions that tell the fascinating past of this country.

We will then visit the Al Fateh Mosque to admire its extraordinary architecture. Subsequently we will head towards the vibrant Bahrain Souq, a typical market, where you can browse among the stalls and buy souvenirs, spices, fabrics and traditional crafts.

Time permitting, we will also make a photo stop at the Bahrain Fort (or Portuguese Fort) an imposing archaeological site 12 meters high, which preserves seven layers created by different occupants from 2300 BC until the 18th century.

Tour highlights: Bahrain Museum, Bahrain Souq, Bahrain Fort, Al Fateh Mosque.

Note: The itinerary may vary based on traffic conditions.' 
WHERE name = 'MANAMA CITY';

